A security officer has been declared deceased after he was shot in the upper body by suspected armed robbers who hit a store in the Madressa Arcade on Yusuf Dadoo Street (Grey Street) this morning, Wednesday 6 February.
According to reports, two suspects hit a store in the arcade and the foot security attempted to halt them. It is believed that the gun-wielding suspects fired a shot which struck the security officer in the upper body, killing him. It is believed that a vehicle was also found abandoned on scene.
Rescue Care’s Garrith Jamieson, said, “It appears that the unknown gunmen were alleged suspects. There was an altercation and the security guard was fatally shot. He was declared deceased on scene.”
SAPS was on scene and are investigating further.